The paper deals with the design of communication-efficient Byzantine Agreement protocols, which is a problem in distributed computing. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses the security of these protocols, which involves cryptographic techniques, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) another likely category. The paper also involves information theory and complexity theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) likely categories. Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of lower bounds, which is a topic in algorithms and data structures, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible category as well.
